1
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:24,773
Mistress Frieren.

2
00:00:27,705 --> 00:00:28,705
You took your time.

3
00:00:30,172 --> 00:00:31,796
So, you defeated Aura.

4
00:02:22,657 --> 00:02:23,818
I don't believe what I see.

5
00:02:24,398 --> 00:02:25,838
I thought this day would never come.

6
00:02:26,339 --> 00:02:27,339
Hurry along.

7
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,520
Stop there.

8
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,001
Don't flee on my behalf.

9
00:02:31,221 --> 00:02:31,862
Good news.

10
00:02:31,902 --> 00:02:33,502
The old softie said he would pardon you.

11
00:02:36,664 --> 00:02:41,666
It must have been a fierce battle, but
none of them are seriously damaged.

12
00:02:45,388 --> 00:02:50,971
I thank you for treating the long-fallen heroes
of the Northern Lands with such immense respect.

13
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:58,778
I used to cast flashy and destructive
spells, but Himmel would always throw a fit.

14
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,179
The man had every right to.

15
00:03:01,659 --> 00:03:02,900
We should all respect the dead.

16
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:04,460
I'd be angry too.

17
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:08,142
For all I've learned about your
nature, Mr. Himmel trained you well.

18
00:03:08,302 --> 00:03:09,742
You mustn't say it like that.

19
00:03:10,783 --> 00:03:12,984
Though I do suppose you have a point.

20
00:03:16,605 --> 00:03:18,586
This is a perfectly normal reaction.

21
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:20,867
What do you mean by that?

22
00:03:22,107 --> 00:03:23,428
Just talking to myself.

23
00:03:25,004 --> 00:03:26,004
Fern?

24
00:03:26,385 --> 00:03:27,385
Stark?

25
00:03:27,745 --> 00:03:29,826
Good work besting
Lügner and his lackey.

26
00:03:30,707 --> 00:03:31,707
I'm proud.

27
00:03:36,349 --> 00:03:39,010
Though I would be more
impressed if you weren't so beat up.

28
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:40,751
This is normal stuff for a warrior.

29
00:03:41,291 --> 00:03:43,132
Just what does normal mean to you?

30
00:03:43,472 --> 00:03:44,833
You look like death itself.

31
00:03:45,473 --> 00:03:47,074
See, they receive proper burials.

32
00:03:47,694 --> 00:03:49,295
I can escort our heroes from here.

33
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:50,875
Sir.

34
00:03:51,136 --> 00:03:52,136
The Lord.

35
00:03:53,337 --> 00:03:54,337
What is it?

36
00:04:05,981 --> 00:04:11,087
Frieren, I've never been so
grateful as I am to you today.

37
00:04:25,619 --> 00:04:31,701
Frieren, for all that you've done for our
city, I vowed to repay you in any way I could.

38
00:04:33,741 --> 00:04:35,041
You requested one thing.

39
00:04:35,802 --> 00:04:39,191
Flamme's grimoire detailing
the defensive barrier, an artifact

40
00:04:39,215 --> 00:04:42,603
that's been passed down my
family tree for generations on end.

41
00:04:43,904 --> 00:04:47,905
Before it's too late to take back your
request, you should know this grimoire

42
00:04:48,025 --> 00:04:49,025
I know, it's fake.

43
00:04:51,548 --> 00:04:52,548
That's correct.

44
00:04:52,588 --> 00:04:54,409
Though it does describe a type of barrier.

45
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,789
It's nothing like the one
that protects our walls.

46
00:04:57,109 --> 00:04:58,730
That spell is passed by tongue.

47
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:01,350
I am well aware of that, my lord.

48
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:03,171
It's just for a hobby of mine.

49
00:05:04,491 --> 00:05:05,491
I see.

50
00:05:06,511 --> 00:05:09,412
Whatever the case, there's no
reason to be so formal with me.

51
00:05:10,272 --> 00:05:13,373
Through your eyes, I must look
like a babe fresh out of the cradle.

52
00:05:14,155 --> 00:05:18,216
I've known better than to test nobility
since my departure to defeat the Demon King.

53
00:05:19,036 --> 00:05:19,856
That sounds right.

54
00:05:20,057 --> 00:05:21,917
Master Heiter mentioned the capital.

55
00:05:22,417 --> 00:05:25,378
How disrespecting nobility
there is punishable by death.

56
00:05:26,158 --> 00:05:30,939
Himmel and Eisen nearly lost their heads for
daring to speak so casually to His Majesty.

57
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,280
Takes me back.

58
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,600
Proud Himmel whimpering like a kitten.

59
00:05:37,061 --> 00:05:39,401
Execution sounds like
overkill, don't you think?

60
00:05:40,542 --> 00:05:41,802
And watch your tone with me.

61
00:05:42,465 --> 00:05:45,506
The way that you've spoken
thus far is a serious offense.

62
00:05:46,087 --> 00:05:47,087
Sorry, old-timer.

63
00:05:47,507 --> 00:05:49,388
You better kiss your fancy chair goodbye.

64
00:05:50,488 --> 00:05:54,030
Well, I'm glad you aren't like those
barbaric central landers, my lord.

65
00:05:58,572 --> 00:06:00,293
You've gotta be kidding me!

66
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:01,493
My work is done.

67
00:06:01,593 --> 00:06:02,593
Trees are pruned.

68
00:06:02,794 --> 00:06:03,794
Thank you.

69
00:06:05,395 --> 00:06:06,395
Don't worry, kid.

70
00:06:07,176 --> 00:06:09,977
I only said that so you wouldn't
waste valuable time saving me.

71
00:06:10,838 --> 00:06:14,519
I won't chop your head off or throw you
in jail for forgetting your sirs and mams.

72
00:06:15,799 --> 00:06:17,080
So relax, adventurers.

73
00:06:18,180 --> 00:06:19,200
Much appreciated.

74
00:06:20,181 --> 00:06:21,181
Say thank you.

75
00:06:21,221 --> 00:06:22,221
You're the one who...

76
00:06:25,202 --> 00:06:26,402
He's petrified.

77
00:06:32,964 --> 00:06:35,745
Naturally, I told the
townsfolk of Aura's defeat.

78
00:06:37,045 --> 00:06:39,846
Of course, they all want a
chance to honor their heroes.

79
00:06:40,754 --> 00:06:42,254
I do hope you'll linger a while.

80
00:06:51,976 --> 00:06:55,673
Whoa, he's floating!

81
00:06:55,697 --> 00:06:59,894
Come on, I did what anybody would do.

82
00:06:59,918 --> 00:07:00,918
Water.

83
00:07:11,775 --> 00:07:12,796
Oh, yes, I see cool.

84
00:08:23,629 --> 00:08:24,651
The shopping's all done.

85
00:08:26,552 --> 00:08:27,032
Perfect.

86
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:28,433
Are we ready to go?

87
00:08:29,354 --> 00:08:30,270
Leaving so soon.

88
00:08:30,294 --> 00:08:31,555
A shame.

89
00:08:32,355 --> 00:08:33,355
Graf Granat.

90
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:36,197
Please, allow me to see you to the gates.

91
00:08:41,461 --> 00:08:48,069
Frieren, I hear you're traveling to Enda, home to the
Demon King's castle and as far north as you can get.

92
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:54,256
You should know, conditions on the Northern
Plateau right now won't make for easy passage.

93
00:08:55,397 --> 00:08:56,819
Travel is heavily restricted.

94
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:02,025
Even the most experienced adventurers
must be accompanied by a first-class mage.

95
00:09:03,465 --> 00:09:04,465
Then we'll be fine.

96
00:09:04,706 --> 00:09:06,706
Clearly Mistress Frieren qualifies.

97
00:09:07,206 --> 00:09:09,467
What do you mean, first-class mage?

98
00:09:10,068 --> 00:09:11,068
Very funny.

99
00:09:11,628 --> 00:09:12,628
You must know.

100
00:09:13,129 --> 00:09:16,786
It's a certification awarded by
the Continental Magic Association.

101
00:09:16,810 --> 00:09:18,487
A certification?

102
00:09:18,511 --> 00:09:21,472
I got mine right before
we left the Holy Capital.

103
00:09:22,952 --> 00:09:23,172
See?

104
00:09:23,552 --> 00:09:26,034
This declares me a
certified third-class mage.

105
00:09:26,634 --> 00:09:29,596
Come to think of it, I do remember
you having some business.

106
00:09:29,896 --> 00:09:32,277
This is what your generation's
certificates look like?

107
00:09:32,557 --> 00:09:36,779
Mistress Frieren, please don't tell me
you're an unlicensed underground mage.

108
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:39,561
You make it sound like
I'm some back-alley doctor.

109
00:09:40,321 --> 00:09:43,563
The organizations that regulate
mages are constantly changing.

110
00:09:43,943 --> 00:09:46,905
I can't obtain a new certification
every time they bat an eye.

111
00:09:48,005 --> 00:09:51,127
I imagine the usefulness of
this holy emblem has expired.

112
00:09:52,623 --> 00:09:54,745
That would sell as an antique.

113
00:09:55,566 --> 00:09:58,228
Even I know about the
Continental Magic Association.

114
00:09:58,948 --> 00:10:01,411
They've been around for over
half a century at the very least.

115
00:10:02,211 --> 00:10:03,733
Exactly, no time at all.

116
00:10:04,974 --> 00:10:08,116
It's a hassle when they change their
standards of conduct so frequently.

117
00:10:09,237 --> 00:10:12,556
In any case, we need to solve
this problem if we want to continue.

118
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:20,580
I don't know the name of the exact town, but if I remember correctly,
there's a place up north where she could take the exam, right?

119
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,382
That'd be the largest magical
city in the Northern Lands.

120
00:10:25,143 --> 00:10:26,464
Its name is Äußerst.

121
00:10:28,005 --> 00:10:29,806
It's far past the Schwer Mountains.

122
00:10:31,107 --> 00:10:34,650
You could follow the beaten path, but
your journey would be arduously long.

123
00:10:39,353 --> 00:10:43,417
Frieren, the House of Granat
will never forget what you've done.

124
00:10:46,619 --> 00:10:47,619
Safe travels.

125
00:11:01,439 --> 00:11:02,439
Hey, it's snowing.

126
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,420
It is almost winter.

127
00:11:06,301 --> 00:11:08,582
An incredibly bitter
season around these parts.

128
00:11:09,622 --> 00:11:10,942
Make light of it and you're dead.

129
00:11:11,543 --> 00:11:13,104
Will it really be that dangerous?

130
00:11:14,464 --> 00:11:15,505
So you aren't aware?

131
00:11:16,265 --> 00:11:22,888
In the war against the Demon King, it wasn't the enemy that
took the most lives, but the winters of the Northern Lands.

132
00:11:30,325 --> 00:11:31,325
Oh, goody.

133
00:11:31,686 --> 00:11:32,686
Seems we're next.

134
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:38,410
What now?

135
00:11:46,135 --> 00:11:47,135
We're lost.

136
00:11:47,996 --> 00:11:51,478
And worse still, we're lost before
even entering the Schwer Mountains.

137
00:11:51,998 --> 00:11:52,998
How pitiful.

138
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,261
Mr. Stark, you need to wake up.

139
00:11:56,861 --> 00:11:57,882
Sleeping will kill you.

140
00:11:59,624 --> 00:12:03,648
You really expect me to believe that Jumbo
Berry Special has always been this small?

141
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,429
We have bigger issues than that.

142
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:07,851
What should we do?

143
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:12,596
The strength of the wind takes any sort of
magical transportation out of the question.

144
00:12:13,417 --> 00:12:14,994
He'd be blown across the sky.

145
00:12:15,018 --> 00:12:18,882
Then I suppose we'll have to carry him.

146
00:12:26,104 --> 00:12:30,082
Goodness, he's a lot heavier
than I thought he would be.

147
00:12:30,106 --> 00:12:32,968
You smell nice.

148
00:12:33,408 --> 00:12:34,568
Can we just leave him?

149
00:12:34,949 --> 00:12:35,949
Not quite yet.

150
00:12:36,329 --> 00:12:39,071
There should be an emergency
shelter at the foot of the mountains.

151
00:12:40,091 --> 00:12:42,549
And you know this from... 80 years ago?

152
00:12:42,573 --> 00:12:44,874
Are you sure it'll still be there?

153
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:53,458
Excellent.

154
00:12:54,079 --> 00:12:56,840
It looks to me like it's being
maintained quite regularly.

155
00:13:02,201 --> 00:13:04,142
Somebody must have
gotten here before us.

156
00:13:04,542 --> 00:13:06,223
We don't know if they're friend or foe.

157
00:13:06,763 --> 00:13:08,063
At this point, who cares?

158
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:10,304
I'd take either over freezing to death.

159
00:13:15,826 --> 00:13:17,246
Yep, heating up.

160
00:13:17,946 --> 00:13:19,127
I'm warmer already!

161
00:13:26,394 --> 00:13:27,395
Pardon the intrusion.

162
00:13:31,277 --> 00:13:32,277
Not a chance.

163
00:13:32,398 --> 00:13:33,698
We need to keep looking around.

164
00:13:33,838 --> 00:13:34,979
We cannot stay here.

165
00:13:35,459 --> 00:13:35,579
Huh?

166
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,380
Why not?

167
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,541
Because there's a pervert inside.

168
00:13:39,662 --> 00:13:40,662
Pervert, you say?

169
00:13:40,742 --> 00:13:41,742
That's not nice.

170
00:13:43,684 --> 00:13:45,045
Come on, Mistress Frieren.

171
00:13:45,285 --> 00:13:45,761
Let's go.

172
00:13:45,785 --> 00:13:47,466
Hold on.

173
00:13:48,107 --> 00:13:49,107
Are you an elf?

174
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:58,252
It's been about three hundred years
since I've met another of my kind.

175
00:13:59,092 --> 00:14:01,172
I thought the last of the
elves had already died out.

176
00:14:02,314 --> 00:14:03,314
I thought so, too.

177
00:14:04,476 --> 00:14:05,476
Thank you, miss.

178
00:14:05,617 --> 00:14:06,677
I appreciate the fire.

179
00:14:07,718 --> 00:14:08,718
Sure.

180
00:14:08,999 --> 00:14:11,280
I'm lucky that it was you
mages who knocked at the door.

181
00:14:12,981 --> 00:14:14,923
The goddess must have
led you straight to me.

182
00:14:15,983 --> 00:14:19,866
I made it through the Sphere Mountains, but as
you'd expect, this blizzard put out my coals.

183
00:14:20,673 --> 00:14:22,954
The hut was a great find,
but freezing, nonetheless.

184
00:14:23,614 --> 00:14:25,194
I was doing squats to stay alive.

185
00:14:26,054 --> 00:14:26,631
I understand.

186
00:14:26,655 --> 00:14:29,155
Well, I suppose that
makes one of us, then.

187
00:14:30,416 --> 00:14:31,736
Anyway, I'm Krafft the Monk.

188
00:14:32,316 --> 00:14:32,696
Pleasure.

189
00:14:32,856 --> 00:14:33,917
I'm Frieren the Mage.

190
00:14:34,697 --> 00:14:36,457
I'm Fern, and I'm also a mage.

191
00:14:37,678 --> 00:14:39,298
That's Mr. Stark, the warrior.

192
00:14:41,019 --> 00:14:42,559
You mentioned heading to a relay.

193
00:14:43,139 --> 00:14:44,459
So you're on a journey to heaven?

194
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:46,520
Good on you lot.

195
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:48,020
Most folks aren't so pious.

196
00:14:48,741 --> 00:14:50,021
I'll believe it when I see it.

197
00:14:51,363 --> 00:14:54,826
Mistress Frieren, it
keeps getting even colder.

198
00:15:01,590 --> 00:15:03,912
So warm and so cozy.

199
00:15:05,173 --> 00:15:06,173
Check it out.

200
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:09,792
Now that's the Jumbo
Berry Special I remember.

201
00:15:09,816 --> 00:15:12,078
Hold on.

202
00:15:13,018 --> 00:15:14,019
What happened to me?

203
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:19,203
Last I remember, we
got caught in a blizzard.

204
00:15:35,682 --> 00:15:37,823
Who the heck are you?

205
00:15:39,043 --> 00:15:40,564
Must you be so noisy?

206
00:15:41,624 --> 00:15:44,565
That's no way to thank someone
for donating their body heat.

207
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:46,125
I saved your life.

208
00:15:47,066 --> 00:15:48,066
With your body heat?

209
00:15:51,427 --> 00:15:51,868
Oh, wow.

210
00:15:52,068 --> 00:15:53,288
Nice body for an old guy.

211
00:15:53,748 --> 00:15:54,749
Well, that was blunt.

212
00:15:54,909 --> 00:15:56,629
Can I not appreciate a man's hard work?

213
00:15:57,550 --> 00:15:59,450
It's obvious he's been
training for decades.

214
00:16:01,311 --> 00:16:02,311
Those abs.

215
00:16:02,431 --> 00:16:03,832
He must be seriously strong.

216
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:05,251
I'm Stark.

217
00:16:05,711 --> 00:16:06,711
You are...

218
00:16:07,153 --> 00:16:08,534
They call me Kraft the Monk.

219
00:16:09,675 --> 00:16:14,781
I can't say I've ever heard of you, but you
must be super famous in the monk world, right?

220
00:16:17,804 --> 00:16:20,266
Stark, you should stay
and rest a bit longer.

221
00:16:21,308 --> 00:16:23,470
You two can help me
bring in some food supplies.

222
00:16:24,271 --> 00:16:26,193
My wagon and cargo shouldn't be too far.

223
00:16:29,962 --> 00:16:31,743
Running into you was a real blessing.

224
00:16:32,523 --> 00:16:35,103
I have enough supplies
here to last us for a long while.

225
00:16:36,004 --> 00:16:37,384
Please, use anything you'd like.

226
00:16:38,304 --> 00:16:40,045
That's quite the stockpile you've got.

227
00:16:40,725 --> 00:16:44,106
Trying to cross the Schwerer Mountains
in these conditions would be suicide.

228
00:16:45,086 --> 00:16:46,747
I'm afraid that we're stuck where we are.

229
00:16:49,507 --> 00:16:50,568
I'm curious, Frieren.

230
00:16:51,368 --> 00:16:52,828
Do you have any idea who I am?

231
00:16:53,749 --> 00:16:54,749
Not in the slightest.

232
00:16:55,429 --> 00:16:56,429
I didn't think so.

233
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:58,649
I don't know the first
thing about you either.

234
00:16:59,803 --> 00:17:02,167
She's the mage from the
party that killed the Demon King.

235
00:17:03,009 --> 00:17:04,009
And before that?

236
00:17:05,553 --> 00:17:06,796
What is it you're getting at?

237
00:17:08,038 --> 00:17:09,821
Just that you and I are elves, I suppose.

238
00:17:59,906 --> 00:18:01,447
It's been nearly six months now.

239
00:18:02,547 --> 00:18:07,489
Thanks to you all, we did what most can't and
survived a grueling winter in the northern lands.

240
00:18:09,521 --> 00:18:10,521
Take this.

241
00:18:13,364 --> 00:18:15,045
Please give it to Fern for me, will you?

242
00:18:15,786 --> 00:18:18,327
A fitting token for a
girl as pious as she is.

243
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:21,850
I guess being raised by a
priest would do that to a person.

244
00:18:22,851 --> 00:18:24,492
She never forgets to thank the Goddess.

245
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:28,675
Will you explain to me why you
believe in the Goddess, Kloft?

246
00:18:30,056 --> 00:18:32,558
On one condition, you
explain why you don't.

247
00:18:33,844 --> 00:18:38,251
I find it incredibly odd that, if you
exclude the Age of Mythology, the Goddess

248
00:18:38,275 --> 00:18:42,966
of Creation hasn't shown herself once in
the massively long history of this world.

249
00:18:44,326 --> 00:18:45,326
You're still young.

250
00:18:46,206 --> 00:18:47,826
I used to think the very same way.

251
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:52,687
But these days, I believe the Goddess
exists from the bottom of my heart.

252
00:18:54,168 --> 00:18:57,208
No, it's more like I need her to exist.

253
00:18:58,468 --> 00:19:02,089
Everyone else who knew of my
righteous triumphs, my acts of justice,

254
00:19:02,961 --> 00:19:03,961
They're long gone.

255
00:19:05,783 --> 00:19:10,085
But when I die, I'll go to heaven, and
there the goddess will praise me at last.

256
00:19:11,526 --> 00:19:12,647
You've done well, Kraft.

257
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:13,967
I'm proud.

258
00:19:14,788 --> 00:19:17,369
The life you have lived
was one of great worth.

259
00:19:17,970 --> 00:19:18,970
Good job.

260
00:19:21,612 --> 00:19:23,273
You understand, Frieren.

261
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:26,394
Your path in life has not been easy.

262
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:30,757
For no one to remember everything
you've done is painful and cruel.

263
00:19:31,989 --> 00:19:35,991
To even reach this moment now,
we have lived lives and lives on end.

264
00:19:38,973 --> 00:19:43,375
Kloft, being remembered is
something we all selfishly desire.

265
00:19:44,536 --> 00:19:45,536
You're right.

266
00:19:47,838 --> 00:19:49,679
And how does heaven
play into that picture?

267
00:19:57,103 --> 00:19:58,103
It's no matter.

268
00:19:58,824 --> 00:20:01,325
Tell me about your life,
and I'll tell you about mine.

269
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:04,431
I think every soul needs
someone to praise them.

270
00:20:04,811 --> 00:20:07,652
So if you don't have the
goddess, then I'll do it instead.

271
00:20:12,714 --> 00:20:13,714
Are you surprised?

272
00:20:14,394 --> 00:20:15,051
Absolutely.

273
00:20:15,075 --> 00:20:19,736
I didn't think you're the type to fund the
reconstruction of some little village's orphanage.

274
00:20:22,797 --> 00:20:23,798
At least you're honest.

275
00:20:25,078 --> 00:20:26,999
You know, I was an orphan once, too.

276
00:20:30,970 --> 00:20:36,533
When my time here ends, I'd like to believe the
Goddess will praise me for a life righteously lived.

277
00:20:37,314 --> 00:20:41,056
Are these really such talks to have with
a drink in your hand, oh corrupt priest?

278
00:20:42,537 --> 00:20:43,537
Frieren.

279
00:20:44,658 --> 00:20:47,559
I have to ask, do you feel that
you have someone to praise you?

280
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,897
Wherever did that come from?

281
00:20:49,921 --> 00:20:54,403
I just wonder, who's there to celebrate
you if you don't believe in the Goddess?

282
00:20:55,404 --> 00:20:59,306
I'm sure you figured it out, but if not,
perhaps I could praise you instead.

283
00:21:00,643 --> 00:21:02,704
I haven't done very
much with my life at all.

284
00:21:03,324 --> 00:21:05,445
Certainly nothing I'd
consider praiseworthy.

285
00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:08,946
And what about the constant
suppression of your mana?

286
00:21:11,226 --> 00:21:15,428
If you ask me, the power to do what you do
seems like the result of tremendous effort.

287
00:21:16,828 --> 00:21:19,229
Such skill would take
a lifetime to acquire.

288
00:21:20,489 --> 00:21:21,489
You could tell?

289
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,630
We've traveled together for years.

290
00:21:23,890 --> 00:21:25,531
Now tell me the story of it all.

291
00:21:26,711 --> 00:21:28,552
I can assure you it's not interesting.

292
00:21:29,185 --> 00:21:30,286
I truly don't mind.

293
00:21:30,787 --> 00:21:33,109
And besides, it might
come in handy someday.

294
00:21:33,729 --> 00:21:34,729
How's that?

295
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:35,910
Oh, who can say?

296
00:21:36,251 --> 00:21:39,674
Perhaps I'll have a child who becomes a
mage and can make use of the knowledge.

297
00:21:42,016 --> 00:21:43,638
I thought that priests couldn't marry.

298
00:21:44,619 --> 00:21:46,100
Ha ha ha ha ha!

299
00:21:50,326 --> 00:21:54,868
I can't put my finger on why, but the
goddess attracts the strangest of people.

300
00:21:56,328 --> 00:22:00,386
Afraid I must pass, I've had someone
praise me enough for a lifetime.

301
00:22:00,410 --> 00:22:03,131
I see.

302
00:22:04,171 --> 00:22:07,713
You're lucky to have good
friends, so please cherish them.

303
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:11,554
Well, it's too late.

304
00:22:11,594 --> 00:22:12,594
He's...

305
00:22:17,716 --> 00:22:19,497
He's already made his way to heaven.

306
00:22:20,391 --> 00:22:22,413
No trouble, for you'll meet again.

307
00:22:23,774 --> 00:22:24,774
Yes, you're right.

308
00:22:27,576 --> 00:22:28,857
Well, I'm headed this way.

309
00:22:29,898 --> 00:22:32,760
Frieren, this isn't the last time we'll meet.

310
00:22:33,721 --> 00:22:35,602
I'll see you in a century or two.

311
00:22:39,705 --> 00:22:41,142
Take care of yourself, old man!

312
00:22:41,166 --> 00:22:42,867
Nice getting to know ya!

313
00:22:44,048 --> 00:22:45,409
Thank you for the pendant.

314
00:22:45,990 --> 00:22:47,431
It means very much to me.

